  	<!-- definitions Modal -->
  <div class="modal fade" id="definition" role="dialog">
    <div class="modal-dialog"> 
      <!-- Modal content-->
      <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header">
          <h4 class="modal-title"></h4>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">

          
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer">
          <div class="back"></div>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <script type="text/javascript">
          function spiritual(p){ 
            var html;
            if(p === "Material_Spiritual_Converging"){
                html = "<a style=\"font-weight:700;\" onclick=\"spiritual('Spiritual')\" href=\"#\">Back</a>";
            }else{
                html = "<a style=\"font-weight:700;\" onclick=\"spiritual('Material_Spiritual_Converging')\" href=\"#\">Back</a>";
            }
              var gcontent = content[p];
              var title = p.replace(/_/g, " ");
              var modal = $("#definition");
              modal.find('.modal-title').text(title);
              modal.find('.back').empty();
              $('.modal-body').empty();
              modal.find('.modal-body').append(gcontent);
              if(p === "Spiritual" || p === "Material_Spiritual_Converging"){
                  modal.find('.back').append(html);
              }
            }
          </script>
    </div>
  </div>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
  	<script type="text/javascript" src="libs/boostrap4/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

  	<script type="text/javascript">

  	let content = {
  		Material_Spiritual_Converging: "Material and spiritual substances can be superposed. This means a thing can be a mixture of material and spiritual substance such that it has properties of both at the same time and in the same respect or context. An example of this is a human being. A human has a material body and a spiritual soul.  These parts are not the same and can be separated one from the other, but while they are unified, the human being demonstrates both material and spiritual actions, characteristics and operations. Material objects other than human beings can have spiritual qualities as well. But it takes a spiritual being like a human to reason about them or feel when they\'re converging.<br /><br /><strong>Spiritual & Material Converging</strong>:<br /><br />"+
        "<ol class='converging'><li> You're stranded out at sea and all you have to drink is your own<strong> Urine</strong>. It saves your life.</li>"+ 
        "<li>You hear about an out-of-control <strong>truck</strong> killing 5 people on a busy <strong>sidewalk</strong>.</li>"+
        "<li><strong>You</strong> do the right thing when <strong>you</strong> could have done wrong. Or, <strong>you</strong> do the wrong thing when <strong>you</strong> could have done right.</li>"+
        "<li>You wear a <strong>crucifix</strong> around your neck; you wear a <strong>pentagram</strong> around your neck.</li></ol>",
  		Spiritual: "Spiritual substance means it has no parts and cannot be separated into parts – it\’s unitary.  It can’t be sensed or detected, but it can be thought of.<br />Reason, Happiness, Justice, Will, Evil are examples of spiritual things. You can’t break off a part of any of them to make that part stand alone.<br />Consider Justice in itself. Not acts or circumstances that are just, only the abstract notion of Justice. You can\'t break off a piece of Justice and make it stand on it\'s own. Things are either Just or they’re not. There’s no middle ground.",
        Material: "Material substance is defined as something that has or can be composed of parts, each of which is different than the other. Material things can also be degraded over time or by a person. Cars rust, toys break and so on.
          <br />Bacteria, baseballs and boomerangs are some other material things,
          they’re all around us.",
        Foundation: "To begin to explain how this works, we’ll start with the idea that everything has a foundation. The foundation is the existence and essence of everything -- its being. <br />Next comes the question, what sort of being is it?  If it\’s a substance of some sort, it is either a spiritual or material substance or it’s a combination of the two. It could also be a modification of the substance, and that’s called an \‘accident\’. The color blue, for instance, can modify your shirt. In this way, \'Accident\' modifies a substances but is not a substance itself",
